entry.ptxt: HO2S Heater Control Circuit Low (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Circuit current of A/F sensor (bank-1) heater is lower than 0.8 A for more than 4 sec continuously while control duty ratio of A/F sensor heater is more than 22% with engine running.
HO2S Heater Control Circuit High (Bank 1 Sensor 1)

Circuit current of A/F sensor (bank-1) heater is higher than 10.5 A on duty pulse or 0.8 A on OFF duty pulse for more than 4 sec continuously while control duty ratio of A/F sensor heater is more than 22% with engine running.
HO2S Heater Control Circuit Low (Bank 1 Sensor 2)

Circuit current of HO2S (bank-1) heater is lower than specification (0.16 – 0.28 A depending on battery voltage) for more than 1 sec continuously while control duty of HO2S sensor heater is ON with engine running.
HO2S Heater Control Circuit High (Bank 1 Sensor 2)

Circuit current of HO2S sensor (bank-1) heater is higher than 5 A at ON duty pulse or 0.2 A at OFF duty pulse for more than 1 sec continuously while control duty of HO2S sensor heater is ON with engine running.
HO2S Heater Control Circuit Low (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Circuit current of A/F sensor (bank-2) heater is lower than 0.8 A for more than 4 sec continuously while control duty ratio of A/F sensor heater is more than 22% with engine running.
HO2S Heater Control Circuit High (Bank 2 Sensor 1)

Circuit current of A/F sensor (bank-2) heater is higher than 10.5 A at ON duty pulse or 0.8 A at OFF duty pulse for more than 4 sec continuously while control duty ratio of A/F sensor heater is more than 22% with engine running.
HO2S Heater Control Circuit Low (Bank 2 Sensor 2)

Circuit current of HO2S (bank-2) heater is lower than specification (0.16 – 0.28 A depending on battery voltage) for more than 1 sec continuously while control duty of HO2S sensor heater is ON with engine running.
HO2S Heater Control Circuit High (Bank 2 Sensor 2)

Circuit current of HO2S sensor (bank-2) heater is higher than 5 A at ON duty pulse or 0.2 A at OFF duty pulse for more than 1 sec continuously while control duty of HO2S sensor heater is ON with engine running.
Ratio of MAF sensor signal to estimated MAF based on engine speed and MAP signal is more than 1.3 or less than 0.8 for more than 10 sec.
Mass Air Flow Circuit Low Input
Output voltage of MAF sensor is less than 0.3 V.
Mass Air Flow Circuit High Input
Output voltage of MAF sensor is more than 5 V.
Manifold Absolute Pressure Circuit Low Input
Output voltage of MAP sensor is less than 0.1 V.
Manifold Absolute Pressure Circuit High Input
Output voltage of MAP sensor is more than 4.9 V.
Intake Air Temperature Sensor Circuit Performance
Variation of IAT sensor signal is less than 15 mV even through ECT reaches 75 °C after engine is started with ECT less than 30 °C.
Intake Air Temperature Sensor Circuit Low
Circuit voltage of IAT sensor is less than 0.16 V.
Intake Air Temperature Sensor Circuit High
Circuit voltage of IAT sensor is more than 5.0 V.
Engine Coolant Temperature Circuit Range / Performance
Variation of ECT sensor input voltage is 15 mV or less even though vehicle has been driven for 10 min or more after starting engine.
Circuit voltage of ECT sensor is less than 0.16 V.
Circuit voltage of ECT sensor is more than 5.0 V.
Output voltage of throttle position sensor (main) is lower than 0.3 V.
Output voltage of throttle position sensor (main) is higher than 4.5 V.
O2 Sensor Circuit Slow Response (Bank 1 Sensor 1)

Number of shifting times for A/F sensor signal between rich and lean is less than 13 times in 20 sec while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running.
O2 Sensor Circuit No Activity Detected (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Impedance of A/F sensor element is higher than 67 Ω for more than 20 sec even though A/F sensor heater is turned ON for more than specified time with engine running.
O2 Sensor Circuit Low Voltage (Bank 1 Sensor 2)
Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) is lower than 15 mV for more than 60 sec continuously with engine running except in fuel cut condition.
O2 Sensor Circuit High Voltage (Bank 1 Sensor 2)
Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) is higher than 1.2 V for more than 20 sec continuously with engine running.
O2 Sensor Circuit No Activity Detected (Bank 1 Sensor 2)

Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) is within 0.27 V – 0.35 V for more than 120 sec continuously while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running, or circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) is out of specified range (0.2 V – 0.45 V) during engine being started from cold (ECT less than 40 °C), then warmed up and run.
O2 Sensor Circuit Slow Response (Bank 2 Sensor 1)

Number of shifting times for A/F sensor signal between rich and lean is less than 13 times in 20 sec while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running.
O2 Sensor Circuit No Activity Detected (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Impedance of A/F sensor element is higher than 67 Ω for more than 20 sec even though A/F sensor heater is turned ON for more than specified time with engine running.
O2 Sensor Circuit Low Voltage (Bank 2 Sensor 2)
Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) is lower than 15 mV for more than 60 sec continuously with engine running except in fuel cut condition.
O2 Sensor Circuit High Voltage (Bank 2 Sensor 2)
Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) is higher than 1.2 V for more than 20 sec continuously with engine running.
O2 Sensor Circuit No Activity Detected (Bank 2 Sensor 2)

Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-2) is within 0.27 V – 0.35 V for more than 120 sec continuously while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running, or circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-2) is out of specified range (0.2 V – 0.45 V) during engine being started from cold (ECT less than 40 °C), then warmed up and run.
Total fuel trim (short term + long term fuel trim) is larger than 127% for more than 20 sec, or short term fuel trim is larger than 130% for more than 30 sec.
Total fuel trim (short term + long term fuel trim) is smaller than 71% for more than 20 sec, or short term fuel trim is smaller than 70% for more than 30 sec.
Total fuel trim (short term + long term fuel trim) is larger than 127% for more than 20 sec, or short term fuel trim is larger than 130% for more than 30 sec.
Total fuel trim (short term + long term fuel trim) is smaller than 71% for more than 20 sec, or short term fuel trim is smaller than 70% for more than 30 sec.
Output voltage of throttle position sensor (sub) is lower than 0.55 V.
Output voltage of throttle position sensor (sub) is higher than 4.82 V.

Misfire, which causes catalyst to overheat during 200 engine revolutions, is detected at 2 or more cylinders. (MIL flashes as long as this misfire occurs continuously.) Or Misfire, which affects exhaust emission adversely during 1000 engine revolutions, is detected at 2 or more cylinders.
Misfire, which causes catalyst to overheat during 200 engine revolutions, is detected at 1 cylinder. (MIL flashes as long as this misfire occurs continuously.)
Or Misfire, which affects exhaust emission adversely during 1000 engine revolutions, is detected at 1 cylinder.
Output voltage of knock sensor is less than 1 V for more than 255 ignition times continuously.
Output voltage of knock sensor is more than 4 V for more than 255 ignition times continuously.

CKP sensor outputs signal of less than 15 pulses even through starting motor switch signal is inputted for more than 3 sec continuously or CKP sensor outputs signal of less than 3 pulses for more than 0.2 sec continuously within 2 pulses of CMP sensor signal.
Crankshaft Position Sensor Circuit Range / Performance
CKP sensor outputs signal of less than 10 pulses for continuous 3 times within CKP no-teeth reference signal (120 °C crank angle).

CMP sensor outputs signal of less than 2 pulses even through starting motor switch signal is inputted for more than 3 sec continuously CKP sensor outputs signal of less than 1 pulse for continuous 3 times within CKP no-teeth reference signal (120 °C crank angle).
Camshaft Position Sensor Circuit Range / Performance
CMP sensor signal pattern is different from previously one 20 times or more.
Exhaust Gas Recirculation Flow Insufficient Detected
MAP variation is 0.67 Kpa or less when EGR valve is either opened or closed.
Exhaust Gas Recirculation Flow Excessive Detected
MAP variation is 8.7 Kpa or more when EGR valve is either opened or closed.
EGR valve control duty pulse monitor signal is less than 0.8 V at OFF duty pulse or more than 2.2 V at ON duty pulse for more than 4 times.

Correlation coefficient that is calculated on the basis of A/F sensor signal and HO2S-2 signal exceeds specification when switched from RICH to LEAN in A/F diagnostic frequency under prescribed running condition.

Correlation coefficient that is calculated on the basis of A/F sensor signal and HO2S-2 signal exceeds specification when switched from RICH to LEAN in A/F diagnostic frequency under prescribed running condition.
Evaporative Emission System Purge Control Valve Circuit Open
EVAP canister purge valve control duty (on 48% ON duty or less) is continuous 240 pulses or more and purge valve circuit voltage is 3.0 V or less during OFF duty pulse condition.
Evaporative Emission System Purge Control Valve Circuit Shorted
EVAP canister purge valve control duty (on 50% ON duty or less) is continuous 240 pulses or more and purge valve circuit voltage is 8.4 V or more during OFF duty pulse condition.
Circuit voltage of fuel level sensor is less than specification calculated from battery voltage.
Circuit voltage of fuel level sensor is more than specification calculated from battery voltage.
No.1 radiator cooling fan relay circuit voltage is more than 8.4 V at relay ON or less than 3.0 V at relay OFF.
No.2 radiator cooling fan relay circuit voltage is more than 8.4 V at relay ON or less than 3.0 V at relay OFF.
No.3 radiator cooling fan relay circuit voltage is more than 8.4 V at relay ON or less than 3.0 V at relay OFF.
Wheel speed signal (RL and/or RR) is 0.6 mph or less even though signal sent from CAN is 4000 rpm or less with fuel cut condition.
A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor Circuit Low
Output voltage of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor is less than 0.15 V for more than 5 sec.
A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor Circuit High
Output voltage of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor is more than 4.95 V for more than 5 sec.
Internal Control Module Memory Check Sum Error
Data write error or check sum error.
No starter switch signal is inputted for 20 sec or more even though there is CMP sensor input with vehicle speed at 2 km/h or less.
There is starter switch input for 180 sec or more even though engine operates at 600 rpm or more.
Monitor signal of A/C compressor relay is different from command signal.
Intake Manifold Tuning Valve Control Circuit Low
Circuit voltage of intake manifold tuning vacuum solenoid valve is less than specification even if solenoid valve is turned OFF.
Intake Manifold Tuning Valve Control Circuit High
Circuit voltage of intake manifold tuning vacuum solenoid valve is more than specification even if solenoid valve is turned ON.
Input voltage of MAP sensor circuit is lower than the 1 V even though vehicle runs under engine load factor of 43% or more.
Input voltage of MAP sensor circuit is more than the specified 2.7 V even though vehicle runs under engine load factor of 27% or less.
Backup power voltage of internal circuit is lower than 3 V or more than 7 V.

When ECM detects invalid data in transmitted control data by means of CAN from TCM, which indicates that some problem occurred in sensor circuits and its calculated values used for operations such as idle speed control, engine power control and so on by TCM, this DTC is detected by ECM.
Throttle Actuator Control Motor Circuit Range / Performance
Difference between actual throttle valve position and target throttle valve position is more than 2° for more than 2 sec.
Throttle Actuator Control Motor Circuit Low
Power supply voltage of throttle actuator control circuit is lower than 6 V for more than 0.5 sec even if throttle actuator control relay is turned on.
Throttle Actuator Control Motor Circuit High
Power supply current of throttle actuator control circuit is higher than specification for more than 0.5 sec.
Throttle actuator power supply voltage is 3 V or less even though its control relay is turned OFF, or throttle actuator power supply voltage is 8 V or more even though the relay is turned ON.
Throttle Actuator Control Throttle Body Range / Performance
Even though throttle motor control is interrupted (throttle valve default position) at the time of detecting failure in electric throttle body, TP is 12 degrees or more, or MAF is 1400 g/min or more.
Even though throttle motor control is interrupted (throttle valve default position) at the time of IG OFF control, TP is 5 degrees or less, or 15 degrees or more.
Output voltage of pedal position sensor (main) is lower than 0.45 V.
Output voltage of pedal position sensor (main) is higher than 4.8 V.
Output voltage of pedal position sensor (sub) is lower than 0.23 V.
Output voltage of pedal position sensor (sub) is higher than 2.4 V.
Throttle Position Sensor (Main / Sub) Voltage Correlation

Index of correlation between main throttle position sensor and sub throttle position sensor (main throttle position sensor voltage plus sub throttle position sensor voltage minus 4.9 V) is more than 0.2 V.
Pedal Position Sensor (Main / Sub) Voltage Correlation

Index of correlation between the main accelerator pedal position sensor and sub accelerator pedal position sensor (1/2 main accelerator pedal position sensor voltage minus sub accelerator pedal position sensor voltage) is more than 0.28 V.
O2 Sensor Signal Stuck Lean (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Short term fuel trim is higher than 130% for 30 seconds even though HO2S (bank-1) signal voltage is higher than 0.5 V.
O2 Sensor Signal Stuck Rich (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Short term fuel trim is lower than 70% for 30 seconds even though HO2S (bank-1) signal voltage is lower than 0.5 V.
O2 Sensor Signal Stuck Lean (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Short term fuel trim is higher than 130% for 30 seconds even though HO2S (bank-2) signal voltage is higher than 0.5 V.
O2 Sensor Signal Stuck Rich (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Short term fuel trim is lower than 70% for 30 seconds even though HO2S (bank-2) signal voltage is lower than 0.5 V.
Difference between measured barometric pressure and estimated barometric pressure based on MAP is more than 25.3 kPa at engine start.
Barometric pressure sensor voltage is less than 0.1 V for more than 19 sec.
Barometric pressure sensor voltage is more than 5.1 V for more than 5.1 V for more than 19 sec.
O2 Sensor Positive Current Control Circuit / Open (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Impedance of A/F sensor element is higher than 250 Ω for more than 5 sec even though A/F sensor heater is turned ON with engine running.
O2 Sensor Positive Current Control Circuit Low (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (+) terminal is lower than 0.4 V or A/F sensor circuit is shorted between (+) terminal wire and (–) terminal wire with engine running.
O2 Sensor Positive Current Control Circuit High (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (+) terminal is higher than 3.5 V with engine running
O2 Sensor Positive Current Control Circuit / Open (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Impedance of A/F sensor element is higher than 250 Ω for more than 5 sec even though A/F sensor heater is turned ON with engine running.
O2 Sensor Positive Current Control Circuit Low (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (+) terminal is lower than 0.4 V or A/F sensor circuit is shorted between (+) terminal wire and (–) terminal wire with engine running.
O2 Sensor Positive Current Control Circuit High (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (+) terminal is higher than 3.5 V with engine running.
O2 Sensor Negative Current Control Circuit Low (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (–) terminal is lower than 0.4 V with engine running.
O2 Sensor Negative Current Control Circuit High (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (–) terminal is higher than 3.5 V with engine running.
O2 Sensor Negative Current Control Circuit Low (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (–) terminal is lower than 0.4 V with engine running.
O2 Sensor Negative Current Control Circuit High (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Circuit voltage of A/F sensor (–) terminal is higher than 3.5 V with engine running.
O2 Sensor Pumping Current Trim Circuit Low (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Output voltage of A/F sensor adjusting resister is less than 0.1 V for more than 4 sec continuously with engine running.
O2 Sensor Pumping Current Trim Circuit High (Bank 1 Sensor 1)
Output voltage of A/F sensor adjusting resister is more than 5 V for more than 4 sec continuously with engine running.
O2 Sensor Pumping Current Trim Circuit Low (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Output voltage of A/F sensor adjusting resister is less than 0.1 V for more than 4 sec continuously with engine running.
O2 Sensor Pumping Current Trim Circuit High (Bank 2 Sensor 1)
Output voltage of A/F sensor adjusting resister is more than 5 V for more than 4 sec continuously with engine running.

Amplitude index of A/F sensor signal between rich and lean is more than 1.3 or less than 0.7 while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running.

Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) signal is less than 0.35 V while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running, or Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-1) signal is more than 0.2 V for more than 4 sec even though vehicle is running with fuel cut mode below 4000 rpm.

Amplitude index of A/F sensor signal between rich and lean is more than 1.3 or less than 0.7 while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running.

Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-2) signal is less than 0.35 V while A/F (fuel trim) is shifted from rich to lean and lean to rich with specified diagnosis frequency under specified running, or Circuit voltage of HO2S (bank-2) signal is more than 0.2 V for more than 4 sec even though vehicle is running with fuel cut mode below 4000 rpm.
Transmission error that is inconsistent between transmission data and transmission monitor (CAN bus monitor) data is detected more than 7 times continuously.
Reception error of communication data for TCM is detected for longer than specified time continuously.
Lost Communication With Electronic Stability Program / ABS Control Module
Reception error of communication data for ABS or ESP® control module is detected for longer than specified time continuously.
Lost Communication With Body Control Module
Reception error of communication data for BCM is detected for longer than specified time continuously.
Refer to Diagnostic Trouble Code (DTC) Table .
ID Code Does Not Registered (Vehicle Equipped with Keyless Start System Only)
Different Registration ID Codes (Vehicle Equipped with Keyless Start System Only)
CAN Communication Error (Reception Error for Keyless Start Control Module) (Vehicle Equipped with Keyless Start System Only)
